NAME
       open - open or create a file

SYNOPSIS
       #include <fcntl.h>

       int open(const char *path, int flags, mode_t mode);

DESCRIPTION
       Opens the file at path with the given flags. If O_CREAT is set
       and the file does not exist, it is created with mode (after
       u-mask). The returned file descriptor is the lowest unused
       integer for the calling task.

FLAGS
       O_RDONLY   read only
       O_WRONLY   write only
       O_RDWR     read and write
       O_CREAT    create if missing
       O_APPEND   append on every write
       O_TRUNC    truncate to 0 if opening writable
       O_NONBLOCK marks the fd non-blocking (TTYs respect this through
                  the TIOCSNONBLOCK ioctl, not the flag directly)

RETURN VALUE
       File descriptor (>= 0) on success, -1 on error.

ERRORS
       ENOENT     no such file and O_CREAT not set
       EISDIR     trying to write a directory
       EACCES     permission denied
       ENOTDIR    a component of path is not a directory

SEE ALSO
       close(2), read(2), write(2), fcntl(2)
